Name: CAN first driver ID
IO Explanation and Notes:
FMS parameter SPN 1625
a. Driver 1 idetification delimiter (ASCII '*'), b. Driver 2 identification delimiter (ASCII '*')
If only one driver card 1 is present, only the parameter driver 1 identification and two delimiters shall be transmitted.
If only driver card 2 is present, a delimiter followed by parameter driver 2 identification and the second delimiter shall be transmitted.
If no driver cards are present, only the two delimiters shall be sent.

Name: CAN second driver ID
IO Explanation and Notes:
FMS parameter SPN 1626
a. Driver 1 idetification delimiter (ASCII '*'), b. Driver 2 identification delimiter (ASCII '*')
If only one driver card 1 is present, only the parameter driver 1 identification and two delimiters shall be transmitted.
If only driver card 2 is present, a delimiter followed by parameter driver 2 identification and the second delimiter shall be transmitted.
If no driver cards are present, only the two delimiters shall be sent.

Name: Trailers Status1
IO Explanation and Notes:
Bitmap (only the first two bits contain actual information on each byte):
Byte pos 1 - Vehicle ABS status: 00 - vehicle ABS passive, but installed, 01 - vehicle ABS active, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 2 - Vehicle service brake status: 00 - vehicle service brake passive, 01 - vehicle service brake active, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 3 - VDC active: 00 - VDC passive, 01 - VDC active, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 4 - Vehicle electrical supply status: 00 - electrical supply insufficient, 01 - electrical supply sufficient, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 5 - External brake request status: 00 - no external brake request active, 01 - external brake request active, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 6 - Braking via electric control line support: 00 - braking via electrical control line not supported, 01 - braking via electrical control line supported, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 7 - Electrical supply of non-braking system status: 00 - supply of non-braking systems off, 01 - supply of non-braking systems on, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 8 - Electrical load proportional function installation status: 00 - vehicle without electrical load proportional function, 01 - vehicle with electrical load proportional function, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed

Name: Trailers Status2
IO Explanation and Notes:
Bitmap (only the first two bits contain actual information on each byte):
Byte pos 1 - Vehicle type: 00 - towing or towed vehicle, 01 - converter dolly axle, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 2 - Stop lamps request: 00 - Stop lamps illumination not requested, 01 - Stop lamps illumination requested, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 3 - Red warning signal request: 00- Red warning signal off, 01 - red warning signal on, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 4 - Amber warning signal request: 00 - Amber warning signal off, 01 - Amber warning signal on, 10 - Amber warning signal flashing, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 5 - Vehicle pneumatic supply status: 00 - Vehicle pneumatic supply insufficient, 01 - Vehicle pneumatic supply sufficient, 10 - error indicator, 11 - not available or not installed
Byte pos 6-8 - Empty

6B to 7B -> CAN1 group: VAG = 1,MERCEDES = 2,CITROEN = 3,FORD = 4,FIAT = 5,OPEL = 6,RENAULT = 7,TOYOTA = 8,TRACTOR = 9,TRUCK = 10,HYUNDAI = 11,LEXUS = 12,VOLVO = 13,BMW = 14,NISSAN = 15,HONDA = 16,MITSUBISHI = 17,SUBARU = 18,CHRYSLER = 19,ISUZU = 20,SSANGYONG = 21,MAZDA = 22,KOMATSU = 23,RANGEROVER = 24,CLAAS = 25,SAAB = 26,LANDROVER = 27,PORSCHE = 28,KIA = 29,JAGUAR = 30,INFINITI = 31,LINDE = 32,HITACHI = 33,SUZUKI = 34

Name: CAN Interface configuration
IO Explanation and Notes:
0b to 7b->CAN Interface parameters:
0b -> CAN2 mode: 0 – silent, 1 – active (MSB)
1b ->CAN2 Auto baud rate: 0 – off, 1 - on.
2b -> CAN2 FF filters: 0 – off, 1 - on.
3b -> CAN2 activity: 0 – inactive, 1 - active.
4b -> CAN1 mode: 0 – silent, 1 - active.
5b ->CAN1 Auto baud rate: 0 – off, 1 - on.
6b -> CAN1 FF filters: 0 – off, 1 - on.
7b -> CAN1 activity: 0 – inactive, 1 - active.
8b to 11b -> CAN2 interface:
0 – NONE.
1 – FMS = 1.
2 – LCV = 2.
3 – OBD = 3.
4 – TACHO.
5 – MOBILEYE.
6 – TRAILERS.
7 – DXP.
12b to 15b -> CAN1 interface:
0 – NONE.
1 – FMS = 1.
2 – LCV = 2.
3 – OBD = 3.
4 – TACHO.
5 – MOBILEYE.
6 – TRAILERS.
7 – DXP.

Name: Trailer tires pressure
IO Explanation and Notes:
First Byte - First axle, Left inner tire
Second Byte - First axle, Right inner tire
Third byte - Second axle, Left inner tire
Fourth byte - Second axle, Right inner tire
Fifth byte - Third axle, Left inner tire
Sixth byte - Third axle, Right inner tire
7-8 B - reserved
Multiplier is 10 kPa/bit, so the maximum possible value for each tire is 2500 kPa

Name: Trailers Axle and total load
IO Explanation and Notes:
Bytes 1-2 - First axle load
Bytes 3-4 - Second axle load
Bytes 5-6 - Third axle load
Multiplier for each axle is 0.5 kg/bit, so the maximum possible value for each axle is 32127.5 kg
Bytes 7-8 - Fourth axle load
Multiplier is 2kg/bit, so the maximum possible value for total load is 128510 kg

Name: Trailers Brake Cylinders Pressure
IO Explanation and Notes:
First Byte - First axle, left
Second Byte - First axle, right
Third byte - Second axle, left
Fourth byte - Second axle, right
Fifth byte - Third axle, left
Sixth byte - Third axle, right
7-8 B - reserved
Multiplier is 5 kPa/bit, so the maximum possible value for each cylinder is 1250 kPa

ELA DI - 0 at (2.1 - 3.0) V, 1 - at (0 - 0.7) V
Escort DU BLE - depends on DU-BLE firmware version and mode selected. See Escort protocol for DU-BLE sensor sequential number 2
Teltonika EYE - [0-1] - movement state

Name: Beacon 0 sensor
IO Explanation and Notes:
GNOM DDE - pressure, unsigned integer, multiplier 0.1, Units - kPa
GNOM DP - angle, unsigned integer, multiplier 0.1, Units - degrees
ELA DI, ELA MAG, ELA MOV - activation count
Escort TD BLE - Fuel level, arbitraty units
Escort DU BLE - depends on DU-BLE firmware version and mode selected. See Escort protocol for DU-BLE sensor sequential number 3. This value will be multiplied by 10.
Escort TL BLE - Luminous flux (lux)
Teltonika EYE - [0-32767] - movement count

Name: Beacon 0 Frequency
IO Explanation and Notes: DUT-E S7 Frequency (must be multiplied by 0.001 in the server backend to get Hz)

Name: Beacon 0 additional info
IO Explanation and Notes:
Teltonika EYE beacon:
Byte 1 - protocol version
Byte 2 - Bitmap. From most to Least significant bit:
0 – Temperature value presence. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting temperature value.

1 – Humidity value presence. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting humidity value.

2 – Magnetic sensor presence. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting Magnetic sensor value.

3 – Magnetic sensor state (1 magnetic field is detected/0 magnetic field is not detected) Valid value is present only if bit 2 flag is set.

4 – Movement sensor counter. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting movement state and count values.

5 – Movement sensor angle. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting angle roll and pitch values.

6 – Low Battery indication. 0 – Means device battery is from 100 to 15 % (When value changes to 1 Battery level is lower than 15 %.

7 – Battery voltage value presence. 1 Means device is reading and transmitting battery voltage value.

Name: Beacon 0 DTC
IO Explanation and Notes:
DTCs of Technoton sensors:
1 - Fuel temperature. No or incorrect data
64 - Current frequency of sensor's measuring generator is higher by more than 100 Hz, compared to the stored value obtained during the calibration of the sensor's "minimum"
512 - Defective measuring generator. Possible locking of the measuring module pipes
1024 - Low battery charge (<10 %)
2097152 - Real time clock. Clocking is off
16777216 - The device is operating in the manufacturing mode
33554432 - Accelerometer. The system does not respond or is not configured.
67108864 - Pressure sensor. The system does not respond or is not configured.
268435456 - Temperature sensor. The system does not respond or is not configured.
536870912 - Position sensor. No data or incorrect data.

Name: Beacon 0 angle
IO Explanation and Notes:
Teltonika EYE beacon:
Byte 1 - Reserved
Byte 2 - Device pitch (-90 to 90 degrees, 2s complement)
Bytes 3-4 - Device roll (-180 to 180 degrees, 2s complement)

IO Explanation and Notes:
First 4 B is P1 value
Last 4 B is P2 value
For devices with U-blox
P1 is x accuracy in meters
P2 is y accuracy in meters
If any value is >9, FFFFF63C is shown.

For devices with Quectel MC60 (Eco4 S):
P1 - Horizontal position error in meters (HEX)
P2 - Vertical position error in meters (HEX)
If there is no valid fix, FFFFFFFFFFFF9E58 is shown
